Circle of Native Writers and Storytellers with the Elder Achievement Award, and two of his collections of poems, Blackrobe and Between Two Rivers, were nominated for the Pulitzer Prize. Kenny has also been honored with the American Book Award for The Mama Poems. His works have been recognized by National Public Radio, and have drawn the attention of famous figures such as Allen Ginsberg, Jerome Rothenberg, and Carolyn Forché.Maurice Kenny: Celebrations of a Mohawk Writer serves as a comprehensive introduction to Kenny's body of work for readers who may be unfamiliar with his writing. Written by prominent scholars in American Indian literature, the book is divided into two parts: the first is devoted to musings on Kenny's influence, and the second to traditional critical essays using historical, nationalist, Two Spirit, creative, memoir, and tribal-theoretical approaches.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aIndians in literature. 4aAmerican Studies : Indigenous Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Native American.2bisacsh1 aBrooks, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruchac, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDragone, Nicholle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDriskill, Qwo-Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGansworth, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGibson, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKelsey, Penelope Myrtle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKelsey, Penelope Myrtle, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSteinberg, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4htt